##Love in the new crown

Material life reference

By Peng Liangjie
Source: Material Life Reference (ID: WZSHCK)

01.

On January 21, Zhang Wen and his girlfriend set off from Beijing on a high speed train to Wuhan Railway Station, where they changed trains, bidding farewell to Xianning, and his girlfriend returned to Xiaogan, both adjacent to Wuhan. They did not expect Xiaogan to become the only city in Hubei Province to have been hit by the outbreak, nor did they expect it to reach this stage -- as it did in Wuhan before it was shut down.

Zhang Wen and his girlfriend are colleagues, Work Unit on the Tenth Day, the two original arrangement is the eighth day together back to Beijing, or in Wuhan Railway Station to meet by high-speed rail. They had arranged to go back to Beijing to see Detective Chinatown 3, which their girlfriend had been waiting for for so long. She had repeatedly told him that they could watch other movies at home during the New Year, but the movie had to be saved to go back to Beijing and watch with her.

Nobody expected that the film would be cancelled and that Beijing would not be able to return.

Zhang says he doesn't mind writing as a negative role model, either in his intimate relationships or his attitude toward pneumonia this time.

The tickets were already booked. The day before they returned home, news of pneumonia had already begun to simmer, and they had discussed whether to refund their tickets to stay in Beijing for the New Year. His girlfriend's attitude is not to return, she asked a very insightful relative in her hometown in Xiaogan, who told her that the situation was not good; Zhang's attitude is to return, he also asked his college classmates who work in Wuhan, the feedback was that it wasn't that bad, "none of us wear masks. ". Two people have a dispute, repeatedly negotiated the decision: back.

So far, Zhang Wen and his girlfriend have been separated for more than 20 days. The two felt isolated at home, and apart from contacting each other at set times of the day, he would report his every move to his girlfriend, follow the news of the epidemic in each other's cities, and occasionally play pool together online. "I've been in touch more recently than I've been in the last few days, " he says.

Compared to miss, his mood in the self-blame the upper hand, "want to recover from the fault but unable to. ". On Feb. 3, the day she was supposed to return to work, she had a big fight with him after realizing that the ban wasn't going to be lifted and that she had a lot of work to do. Zhang himself also regrets, "now all the consequences are caused by me, " he said after the lifting of the ban to meet the most want to do is solemnly apologize to his girlfriend, although he has apologized countless times in wechat and on the phone.

He recalled another scene: When the high-speed train was approaching Wuhan, his girlfriend changed a new mask and reminded Zhao Wen to change a mask too. It is not good to wear the mask for too long. Zhang Wen's mask on the overhead bin in the suitcase, he did not want to take trouble, his girlfriend said he "do not know dead or alive" , angry ignore him. He finally gave up and put it on.

The self-reflection has finally begun in this period of self-isolation. "I guess I'm one of those self-assured people? Stubborn, not only this time, before the quarrel also often because of this. She told me and I went my own way, always thinking I was right and then hitting me in the face, but next time it was the same."

After this incident, Zhang Wen's desire to get married became strong. He and his girlfriend have known each other for four years. The two originally planned to get married more than a year ago after their girlfriend graduated from graduate school, but it has now dragged on, it was because "on some key issues, I knew I had a problem but kept resisting change and giving her no confidence. "

For the moment, at least, his resolve was unquestioned: "When I get back to Beijing, I'll take my problems seriously, meet my parents, get married. "

Chen Jing is trapped in her boyfriend's village, as Zhang Wen and her girlfriend are separated. On the second day of the Lunar New Year, she and her boyfriend went back to their hometown, a village below Changsha in Hunan Province. They had planned to leave on the fourth day, but they stayed for 14 days because of the road closure.

They both work in Changsha, live far away, work units are also far away, coupled with their recent busy preparation for the exam, a week or two to see each other. The closure of the village, for the first time in a row so many days, 24 hours "living under each other's eyes. ". Chen Jing did not expect that her boyfriend, who "has low emotional intelligence but can not coax people" and "can not say a few words when chatting on Wechat at ordinary times" , would take care of herself like this. She didn't have to do any work. There were a few days when the sun came out and her boyfriend moved out the Sofa in his home, let Chen Jing Bask in the sun and read in the yard.

Her boyfriend joked that it felt like the Movie Blind Mountain, which lured her to the village, where she couldn't escape. Chen recalled the plot of Eileen Chang's Love in a Fallen City, in which Fan Liuyuan and Bai Tassel finally let down their guard amid the roar of the war, i mean it, but I think it's too pessimistic.

Since I didn't plan to stay in my hometown for long, I didn't prepare much food at first. I could pick vegetables at my neighbor's farm, but there wasn't enough meat to eat after the road was closed and there was no place to buy. Chen Jing one day suddenly want to eat meat, boyfriend then proposed to go fishing, fish stew in the evening.

The fishing rod at home is a bit old, the middle section with sticky tape to barely work, floating in the water is always a problem. Chen Jing does not hold any hope, even did not take the bucket of fish, just as this is an entertainment program, to pass the time. Which knows really has the fish to take the bait, she excitedly runs back to take the bucket, the boyfriend mother said, this kind of small crucian carp, catches 8 to be able to make a meal. At the last count, 12 fish were caught in over two hours.

That night, Chen Jing drank the fish soup. Boyfriend's mother with 12 small fish stew a pot of turnip carp soup, turnip is pulled in the neighbor's vegetable plot, "also with the soil fragrant white radish, very delicious. ".

Chen and her boyfriend had discussed getting married before, and they planned to register as soon as they had enough money for a down payment on a car. The boyfriend is looking for the Toyota Toyota Camry, more than 200,000,60,000 each, is also the motivation to work hard.

"He's not going to pop the question on Valentine's Day, is he? " I asked nosy.
"Who knows if he has played tricks recently. " Chen Jing answered with a smile.

02.

Marriage was also tested by the epidemic.

In a world where the virus was contained in time, marriage registries in various districts of Wuhan were packed with couples following a good omen on February 2,2020. This Day is the first weekend after the Spring Festival holiday and a legal rest day. However, due to the special day of "World Symmetry Day" , civil affairs systems in cities across the country announced in January that they would open their doors on this day, to the hearts of those who love you.

But now, the whole city is quiet.

All over the country, February 2 was scheduled to open the marriage registration day have been cancelled. The city released the Figures: On Feb. 2,5,200 couples were booked for marriage registration. The Wedding Registration Day, which was opened for special circumstances, had to be cancelled because of "special circumstances" . It seemed to remain the same, but everything changed.

A Weibo user from Guangdong Province posted a reminder that the appointment had been canceled, "to commemorate the Registration Day of the original appointment. ". The last post was at the top, a happy moment recorded a month ago:

After February 2, some cities simply announced the suspension of marriage registration, "resumption of time until further notice" , some cities in the form of online reservation to limit the flow of people to avoid gathering.

Not only is the marriage registration, the wedding ceremony can not be held as scheduled, the New People sent out the invitation card can only be canceled. Only a handful of bloggers have called for a vote and insisted that it not be cancelled.

A friend who runs a bridal studio in Hubei told me that the Spring Festival has always been a small peak season for weddings. According to the bookings made before the Spring Festival, there have been weddings since the sixth day of the Lunar New Year. The studio has five employees, and if business doesn't pick up in the next few months, it's likely that the studio plans to stream makeup classes online to increase revenue, as well as pay rent and salaries.

But she is not pessimistic about the industry's prospects, judging that more people will decide to get married after the epidemic is over.

However, what one sees is the other side of the epidemic -- as many have asserted, this home based quarantine will spawn an army of divorcees. Many of the comments, under articles about the topic by some of the most influential people in the country, have been poignant; some on Zhihu couldn't wait to ask when the civil affairs bureau would resume divorce proceedings.

The mask as the current name worthy of the "hard currency" , in the marriage also became a measure of the depth of the feelings of the mask in hand, keep a few, give your family a few, my family a few, it all points to the ultimate question of whether or not to love or not to care.

Earlier, a video of a speech by Zhang Wenhong, director of the Infectious Diseases Department of the Mount Hua Hospital affiliated to Fudan University, went viral with the headline: Virus Hunter Zhang Wenhong: I no longer believe in love, it was taken from a joke Zhang mentioned in the speech:

For example, if a girl is sick, it may infect her husband, it may infect her mother, but among the patients I see, the rate of infection in their own family is very low, no more than 10% , most of the 10% infected their mother, but not their husband, so in that moment, I had doubts about love.

03.

There is a love story in the novel "the plague" that has been skipped over. That was when the city of Oran declared a rat-infested siege, with only entry and no exit, and with only a short window of opportunity. It was thought to be an ill advised act by a couple in love, but it was an old couple -- an old lady on her way out of town before the plague -- heading back to Oran to fight the unknown with her husband, because they realized they couldn't live without each other.

As we wrote earlier about a Wuhan couple in their 60s, Zhao Ping and Feng An. In early January, Zhao contracted the disease, and her husband, Feng An, was subsequently infected because hospital beds were inadequate and she had to be quarantined at home. "At the beginning, we were careful to separate our eating bowls, to keep our conversation at arm's length, to disinfect our toilets, to sleep in one room, but how can we be completely isolated when the couple live in the same room? Now both of them are infected, forget it, let's not hide it,"said Zhao Ping.

Two people go to the hospital every day early and late to line up for infusion, Feng an in order to let his wife sleep for a while, get up at five in the morning to go first row, Zhao Ping eight past.

In early February, after Wuhan announced that it would concentrate on patients without beds, the community arranged for the couple to be quarantined. Feng an because the test result is positive, first went to the hotel isolation, Zhao Ping at this time has recovered almost, and the test result is negative, oneself stay at home. She had been told by the community the previous day that she too must be quarantined, or else the gate would be sealed and no one would be allowed in or out. Zhao Ping thought now anyway is also a person at home, as well as to quarantine it.

She was placed on the fifth floor of the same hotel, with her husband upstairs, a floor apart, and they communicated daily by phone to check on each other's health. At this time Zhao Ping has been self-reproach, "if I did not infect him, he would not get this disease, his physical quality has always been very good. "

It was a time when people saw the face of Love: The families of the medical staff who sent their loved ones to the front lines of the epidemic; the media people who left a suicide note for their wives; the girl who spent two hours on her bike delivering face masks and alcohol to her boyfriend; Couples forced to stay at home to get to know each other again; young singles who canceled their Spring Festival blind dates because of the epidemic; Doctor Couples who checked each other's protective gear for damage..

Today, February 14,2020, dozens of movies scheduled to be released on Valentine's Day have been pulled from theaters; "cloud dating" has been promoted, causing a $70 billion loss to the nation's restaurant industry in just one day; and one million flowers have been destroyed due to insufficient trading volume, others may not arrive on time -- as a result of logistics

But one netizen said: Valentine's Day in 2020 is the most simple Valentine's Day, after taking off the ceremonial dress and the money packaging of love, we can see the true nature of love.

(the interviewees are all pseudonyms)

"Who knows if he has played tricks recently. " Chen Jing answered with a smile.

On January 21, Zhang Wen and his girlfriend set off from Beijing on a high speed train to Wuhan Railway Station, where they changed trains, bidding farewell to Xianning, and his girlfriend returned to Xiaogan, both adjacent to Wuhan. They did not expect Xiaogan to become the only city in Hubei Province to have been hit by the outbreak, nor did they expect it to reach this stage -- as it did in Wuhan before it was shut down.

Zhang Wen and his girlfriend are colleagues, Work Unit on the Tenth Day, the two original arrangement is the eighth day together back to Beijing, or in Wuhan Railway Station to meet by high-speed rail. They had arranged to go back to Beijing to see Detective Chinatown 3, which their girlfriend had been waiting for for so long. She had repeatedly told him that they could watch other movies at home during the New Year, but the movie had to be saved to go back to Beijing and watch with her.

Nobody expected that the film would be cancelled and that Beijing would not be able to return.

Zhang says he doesn't mind writing as a negative role model, either in his intimate relationships or his attitude toward pneumonia this time.

The tickets were already booked. The day before they returned home, news of pneumonia had already begun to simmer, and they had discussed whether to refund their tickets to stay in Beijing for the New Year. His girlfriend's attitude is not to return, she asked a very insightful relative in her hometown in Xiaogan, who told her that the situation was not good; Zhang's attitude is to return, he also asked his college classmates who work in Wuhan, the feedback was that it wasn't that bad, "none of us wear masks. ". Two people have a dispute, repeatedly negotiated the decision: back.

So far, Zhang Wen and his girlfriend have been separated for more than 20 days. The two felt isolated at home, and apart from contacting each other at set times of the day, he would report his every move to his girlfriend, follow the news of the epidemic in each other's cities, and occasionally play pool together online. "I've been in touch more recently than I've been in the last few days, " he says.

Compared to miss, his mood in the self-blame the upper hand, "want to recover from the fault but unable to. ". On Feb. 3, the day she was supposed to return to work, she had a big fight with him after realizing that the ban wasn't going to be lifted and that she had a lot of work to do. Zhang himself also regrets, "now all the consequences are caused by me, " he said after the lifting of the ban to meet the most want to do is solemnly apologize to his girlfriend, although he has apologized countless times in wechat and on the phone.

He recalled another scene: When the high-speed train was approaching Wuhan, his girlfriend changed a new mask and reminded Zhao Wen to change a mask too. It is not good to wear the mask for too long. Zhang Wen's mask on the overhead bin in the suitcase, he did not want to take trouble, his girlfriend said he "do not know dead or alive" , angry ignore him. He finally gave up and put it on.

The self-reflection has finally begun in this period of self-isolation. "I guess I'm one of those self-assured people? Stubborn, not only this time, before the quarrel also often because of this. She told me and I went my own way, always thinking I was right and then hitting me in the face, but next time it was the same."

After this incident, Zhang Wen's desire to get married became strong. He and his girlfriend have known each other for four years. The two originally planned to get married more than a year ago after their girlfriend graduated from graduate school, but it has now dragged on, it was because "on some key issues, I knew I had a problem but kept resisting change and giving her no confidence. "

For the moment, at least, his resolve was unquestioned: "When I get back to Beijing, I'll take my problems seriously, meet my parents, get married. "

Chen Jing is trapped in her boyfriend's village, as Zhang Wen and her girlfriend are separated. On the second day of the Lunar New Year, she and her boyfriend went back to their hometown, a village below Changsha in Hunan Province. They had planned to leave on the fourth day, but they stayed for 14 days because of the road closure.

They both work in Changsha, live far away, work units are also far away, coupled with their recent busy preparation for the exam, a week or two to see each other. The closure of the village, for the first time in a row so many days, 24 hours "living under each other's eyes. ". Chen Jing did not expect that her boyfriend, who "has low emotional intelligence but can not coax people" and "can not say a few words when chatting on Wechat at ordinary times" , would take care of herself like this. She didn't have to do any work. There were a few days when the sun came out and her boyfriend moved out the Sofa in his home, let Chen Jing Bask in the sun and read in the yard.

Her boyfriend joked that it felt like the Movie Blind Mountain, which lured her to the village, where she couldn't escape. Chen recalled the plot of Eileen Chang's Love in a Fallen City, in which Fan Liuyuan and Bai Tassel finally let down their guard amid the roar of the war, i mean it, but I think it's too pessimistic.

Since I didn't plan to stay in my hometown for long, I didn't prepare much food at first. I could pick vegetables at my neighbor's farm, but there wasn't enough meat to eat after the road was closed and there was no place to buy. Chen Jing one day suddenly want to eat meat, boyfriend then proposed to go fishing, fish stew in the evening.

The fishing rod at home is a bit old, the middle section with sticky tape to barely work, floating in the water is always a problem. Chen Jing does not hold any hope, even did not take the bucket of fish, just as this is an entertainment program, to pass the time. Which knows really has the fish to take the bait, she excitedly runs back to take the bucket, the boyfriend mother said, this kind of small crucian carp, catches 8 to be able to make a meal. At the last count, 12 fish were caught in over two hours.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That night, Chen Jing drank the fish soup. Boyfriend's mother with 12 small fish stew a pot of turnip carp soup, turnip is pulled in the neighbor's vegetable plot, "also with the soil fragrant white radish, very delicious. ".

Chen and her boyfriend had discussed getting married before, and they planned to register as soon as they had enough money for a down payment on a car. The boyfriend is looking for the Toyota Toyota Camry, more than 200,000,60,000 each, is also the motivation to work hard.

"He's not going to pop the question on Valentine's Day, is he? " I asked nosy.

"Who knows if he has played tricks recently. " Chen Jing answered with a smile.

02.

Marriage was also tested by the epidemic.

In a world where the virus was contained in time, marriage registries in various districts of Wuhan were packed with couples following a good omen on February 2,2020. This Day is the first weekend after the Spring Festival holiday and a legal rest day. However, due to the special day of "World Symmetry Day" , civil affairs systems in cities across the country announced in January that they would open their doors on this day, to the hearts of those who love you.

But now, the whole city is quiet.

All over the country, February 2 was scheduled to open the marriage registration day have been cancelled. The city released the Figures: On Feb. 2,5,200 couples were booked for marriage registration. The Wedding Registration Day, which was opened for special circumstances, had to be cancelled because of "special circumstances" . It seemed to remain the same, but everything changed.

A Weibo user from Guangdong Province posted a reminder that the appointment had been canceled, "to commemorate the Registration Day of the original appointment. ". The last post was at the top, a happy moment recorded a month ago:

After February 2, some cities simply announced the suspension of marriage registration, "resumption of time until further notice" , some cities in the form of online reservation to limit the flow of people to avoid gathering.

Not only is the marriage registration, the wedding ceremony can not be held as scheduled, the New People sent out the invitation card can only be canceled. Only a handful of bloggers have called for a vote and insisted that it not be cancelled.

A friend who runs a bridal studio in Hubei told me that the Spring Festival has always been a small peak season for weddings. According to the bookings made before the Spring Festival, there have been weddings since the sixth day of the Lunar New Year. The studio has five employees, and if business doesn't pick up in the next few months, it's likely that the studio plans to stream makeup classes online to increase revenue, as well as pay rent and salaries.

But she is not pessimistic about the industry's prospects, judging that more people will decide to get married after the epidemic is over.

However, what one sees is the other side of the epidemic -- as many have asserted, this home based quarantine will spawn an army of divorcees. Many of the comments, under articles about the topic by some of the most influential people in the country, have been poignant; some on Zhihu couldn't wait to ask when the civil affairs bureau would resume divorce proceedings.

The mask as the current name worthy of the "hard currency" , in the marriage also became a measure of the depth of the feelings of the mask in hand, keep a few, give your family a few, my family a few, it all points to the ultimate question of whether or not to love or not to care.

Earlier, a video of a speech by Zhang Wenhong, director of the Infectious Diseases Department of the Mount Hua Hospital affiliated to Fudan University, went viral with the headline: Virus Hunter Zhang Wenhong: I no longer believe in love, it was taken from a joke Zhang mentioned in the speech:

For example, if a girl is sick, it may infect her husband, it may infect her mother, but among the patients I see, the rate of infection in their own family is very low, no more than 10% , most of the 10% infected their mother, but not their husband, so in that moment, I had doubts about love.

03.

There is a love story in the novel "the plague" that has been skipped over. That was when the city of Oran declared a rat-infested siege, with only entry and no exit, and with only a short window of opportunity. It was thought to be an ill advised act by a couple in love, but it was an old couple -- an old lady on her way out of town before the plague -- heading back to Oran to fight the unknown with her husband, because they realized they couldn't live without each other.

As we wrote earlier about a Wuhan couple in their 60s, Zhao Ping and Feng An. In early January, Zhao contracted the disease, and her husband, Feng An, was subsequently infected because hospital beds were inadequate and she had to be quarantined at home. "At the beginning, we were careful to separate our eating bowls, to keep our conversation at arm's length, to disinfect our toilets, to sleep in one room, but how can we be completely isolated when the couple live in the same room? Now both of them are infected, forget it, let's not hide it,"said Zhao Ping.

Two people go to the hospital every day early and late to line up for infusion, Feng an in order to let his wife sleep for a while, get up at five in the morning to go first row, Zhao Ping eight past.

In early February, after Wuhan announced that it would concentrate on patients without beds, the community arranged for the couple to be quarantined. Feng an because the test result is positive, first went to the hotel isolation, Zhao Ping at this time has recovered almost, and the test result is negative, oneself stay at home. She had been told by the community the previous day that she too must be quarantined, or else the gate would be sealed and no one would be allowed in or out. Zhao Ping thought now anyway is also a person at home, as well as to quarantine it.

She was placed on the fifth floor of the same hotel, with her husband upstairs, a floor apart, and they communicated daily by phone to check on each other's health. At this time Zhao Ping has been self-reproach, "if I did not infect him, he would not get this disease, his physical quality has always been very good. "

It was a time when people saw the face of Love: The families of the medical staff who sent their loved ones to the front lines of the epidemic; the media people who left a suicide note for their wives; the girl who spent two hours on her bike delivering face masks and alcohol to her boyfriend; Couples forced to stay at home to get to know each other again; young singles who canceled their Spring Festival blind dates because of the epidemic; Doctor Couples who checked each other's protective gear for damage..

Today, February 14,2020, dozens of movies scheduled to be released on Valentine's Day have been pulled from theaters; "cloud dating" has been promoted, causing a $70 billion loss to the nation's restaurant industry in just one day; and one million flowers have been destroyed due to insufficient trading volume, others may not arrive on time -- as a result of logistics

But one netizen said: Valentine's Day in 2020 is the most simple Valentine's Day, after taking off the ceremonial dress and the money packaging of love, we can see the true nature of love.
